cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper investigates common assumptions about neural networks, which are central to the field of deep learning. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper evaluates theoretical assumptions about neural networks and their impact on learning. Additionally, the paper explores the behavior of classifiers, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of weight decay and the impact of parameter norms on generalization could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
